3.📡 Handling GET Requests

GET is used to retrieve data

app.get('/about', (req, res) => {
  res.send('About Page');
});
or
app.get('/user', (req, res) => {
  res.send(`User: ${req.query.name}`);
});

📩 Handling POST Requests
POST is used to send data to the server.
app.use(express.json());
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  const { username, password } = req.body;
  res.send(`Welcome ${username}`);
});

📤 Sending Responses

Express provides helpful methods:
res.send('Text response');        // plain text
res.json({ name: 'John' });      // JSON response
res.status(404).send('Not Found'); // status + message


🔁 Routing Concept (Core Idea)

Routing means:
👉 “When a request hits this URL with this method → run this function”

Basic Structure
app.METHOD(PATH, HANDLER);

app.get('/products', handlerFunction);
app.post('/products', handlerFunction);


Client Request
     ↓
Route Match (URL + Method)
     ↓
Route Handler Function
     ↓
Response Sent Back



app
 ├── GET  /        → Home handler
 ├── GET  /about   → About handler
 ├── POST /login   → Login handler
 └── GET  /user    → User handler
